    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S represents a rare opportunity to acquire a preserved example of the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powerplant maintains exceptional thermal efficiency with no signs of housing fatigue, delivering linear boost through the factory-spec Hitachi HT12 turbochargers. The chassis remains structurally rigid, featuring its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and four-piston aluminum calipers for precise threshold braking. Power is managed via a crisp five-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque bias. Recent compression testing confirms high, consistent pulses across all rotor faces, verifying the integrity of the apex seals. This is a mechanically superlative specimen for the collector who prioritizes engineering purity and kinematic excellence.",
